                        <summary
                            class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center outline-none"
                        >
                            <span
                                >Does a Working Holiday Visa count for BC PNP?</span
                            >
                            <span
                                class="transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-180 text-indigo-500"
                                >▼</span
                            >
                        </summary>
                        <div
                            class="mt-4 text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-100 pt-4 animate-fadeIn"
                        >
                            Yes. A Working Holiday Visa (IEC) is an Open Work
                            Permit. It is fully valid for BC PNP as long as you
                            have a qualifying job offer
                            (indeterminate/full-time) from a BC employer.
                        </div>
                    </details>

                    <details
                        class="group bg-slate-50 p-5 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 open:bg-white open:ring-1 open:ring-indigo-100 open:shadow-md transition-all"
                    >
                        <summary
